abstract: Venezuelan Violence Observatory issues report estimating that country had  27,875 homicides  in 2015, pushing rate to 90 per 100,000 residents, up from 82 per 100,000 in 2014; figures make country one of most violent in world.
lead_paragraph: It is estimated that 27,875 killings occurred in Venezuela this year, pushing the homicide rate up to 90 per 100,000 residents; last year, its count was 82 per 100,000.

headline.main: Venezuela: Murder Rate for Year May Be World’s Worst, Report Says
headline.print_headline: The Americas; Venezuela: Murder Rate for Year Among World’s Worst, Report Says
